# QCD predictions for the mMDT mass distribution in bins of the jet pt
# 
# Overview
# --------
# The detailed description of the results below can be found in 
#   A study of jet mass distributions with grooming,
#   Simone Marzani, Lais Schunk and Gregory Soyez 
#   arXiv:1604.ZZZZ
#
# They corresponds to the following setup:
#
#   - we select events with at least two jets (clustered with the
#     anti-kt algorithm with R=0.8) satisfying pt>200 GeV and |y|<2.4
#
#   - We only retain the two hardest jets, j1 and j2, and impose that
#     abs(pt1-pt2)/(pt1+pt2)<0.3 and delta_phi(j1,j2)>pi/2
#
#   - individually on each jet, we then run the modified MassDrop
#     Tagger (aka Soft Drop with beta=0) with zcut=0.1.
#
#   - We measure the mass of the mMDT jet in bins of the pt of the
#     initial jet
#
# Accuracy of the prediction
# --------------------------
# Our theoretical predictions are at the NLO+LL accuracy. This means
# the leading-logarithmic (LL) accuracy in the ratio of the jet mass
# to the jet transverse momentum matched with fixed-order
# cross-sections at NLO.
#
# LL here corresponds to a resummation performed at the
# single-logarithmic accuracy, including contributions from finite
# zcut effects.
#
# Fixed-order results are obtained from the NLOJet++ program using the
# CT14 PDF set (at NLO)
#
# We use a multiplicative-style matching procedure.
#
# The theoretical uncertainty is obtained by varying the
# renormalisation and factorisation scales by a factor of 2 up and
# down (using the 7-point rule) as well as the resummation scale, also
# by a factor of 2 up and down.  The envelope is taken as the
# uncertainty.
#
# We have also included predictions for the non-perturbative
# corrections. These are obtained by taking the average and envelope of
# the particle-level (including both hadronisation and the Underlying Event)
# to parton-level ration given by the following Monte Carlo generators
# and tunes:
#   - Herwig 6.5.21 in the AUET2 tune
#   - Pythia 6.4.28 in the Z2 tune
#   - Pythia 6.4.28 in the Perugia 2011 tune
#   - Pythia 8.223  in the 4C tune
#   - Pythia 8.223  in the Monash 2013 tune
#
# Structure of the results
# ------------------------
# We provide results for both the un-normalised differential
# cross-section dsigma/dm(pt1,pt2) integrated over a bin
# pt1 < pt < pt2 in the jet transverse momentum as well as for the
# normalised distribution (normalised to the total cross-section for
# jets in that pt bin).
#
# Un-normalised cross-sections are given in nb/GeV
# Normalised    cross-sections are given in GeV^{-1}
#
# The bins in pt are as follows:
#    200 < pt <  260 GeV
#    260 < pt <  350 GeV
#    350 < pt <  460 GeV
#    460 < pt <  550 GeV
#    550 < pt <  650 GeV
#    650 < pt <  760 GeV
#    760 < pt <  900 GeV
#    900 < pt < 1000 GeV
#   1000 < pt < 1100 GeV
#   1100 < pt < 1200 GeV
#   1200 < pt < 1300 GeV
#   1300 < pt
#
# For each bin in pt, the results are presented under the following format:
#
#   mass_min mass_central mass_max   sigma_NLO+LL_unnorm_min sigma_NLO+LL_unnorm_central sigma_NLO+LL_unnorm_max   sigma_NLO+LL+NP_unnorm_min sigma_NLO+LL+NP_unnorm_central sigma_NLO+LL+NP_unnorm_max   sigma_NLO+LL_norm_min sigma_NLO+LL_norm_central sigma_NLO+LL_norm_max   sigma_NLO+LL+NP_norm_min sigma_NLO+LL+NP_norm_central sigma_NLO+LL+NP_norm_max
# 
# This is 5 main blocks:
#
#   mass   sigma_NLO+LL_unnorm   sigma_NLO+LL+NP_unnorm   sigma_NLO+LL_norm   sigma_NLO+LL+NP_norm
#
# with 
#   - sigma_NLO+LL_unnorm     the un-normalised perturbative (NLO+LL) cross-section
#   - sigma_NLO+LL+NP_unnorm  the un-normalised cross-section including non-perturbative corrections
#   - sigma_NLO+LL_norm       the normalised perturbative (NLO+LL) cross-section
#   - sigma_NLO+LL+NP_norm    the normalised cross-section including non-perturbative corrections
#
# and where in each case, we provide 3 numbers: the lower value,
# the central value and the upper value (this is valid for both the
# mass bin and the results for the cross-section)
#
